Springbok captain Siya Kolisi has ended his 11-year-career with Western Province, joining the Sharks. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - It's the biggest and most high profile transfer in South African Rugby. Springbok captain Siya Kolisi has ended his 11-year-career with Western Province, joining the Sharks. WATCH: Siya Kolisi unveiled as a Sharks player The next chapter in the career of the Zwide-born flanker, will now be written at Kings Park. There he will find fellow World Cup winners Lukhanyo Am and Makazole Mapimpi. eNCA's Justin Ford sat down with Kolisi in Durban. Watch the interview above. 